# Fall 2016 Schedule
## Default meeting time: Fridays at 3pm, Math & Science Center W201
***

|Date| Speakers| Topics | Materials |
|:---:|---|---|---|
|10/14/2016|Delivering Cat Videos at World Scale: A YouTube Video Delivery Story|Dr. Pawel Jurczyk, Google (Emory CSI PhD'2009)||
|10/7/2016|Summer Internship Reports: Google and YikYak|Clarissa Garvey: software engineer (research) internship at Google
Tomasz Jurczyk: research internship at Yik-Yak (local social media startup)||
|9/30/2016|Building Software for Prediction and Learning with Heterogeneous Cancer Data|Prof. Lee Cooper (BMI)||
|9/23/2016|How to read a CS paper|Prof. Eugene Agichtein and Prof. Ymir Vigfusson||
|9/16/2016|How to succeed as grad student in CS: students and faculty panel|Prof. Lee Cooper, Prof. Ymir Vigfusson, Prof. Jinho Choi, Prof. Li Xiong, Denis Savenkov, Clarissa Garvey, Layla Pournajaf||
|9/9/2016| Research Highlights: Prof. Tianwei Yu, Prof. Ymir Vigfusson, and Prof. Shamim Nemati| Gene network analysis (Yu), Systems (Vigfusson ), ML for Medicine (Nemati) ||
|9/2/2016 | Research Highlights: Prof. Joyce Ho, Prof. Davide Fossati, Prof. Li Xiong | Data Mining (Ho), CS Education (Fossati), Data and Privacy (Xiong) ||
|8/26/2016|Research Highlights: Prof. Lars Ruthotto, Prof. Eugene Agichtein, Prof. Jinho Choi|Inverse Problems (Ruthotto), Information Retrieval and Web Search (Agichtein), Natural Language Processing (Choi)||
